<br>
FV is a Roleplay server, so this should be reflected in the way that we handle these things.  It would seem to me that, generally, Evils would cooperate and Goods would cooperate but that we might fight for contested spawns.  Therefore, the following structure:<br>
<br>
Good/Evil rotation.  With a twist...<br>
<br>
If evils wanted to jump ahead on a spawn claimed by goods, then they could.  All they gotta do is win a guildwar.  Same if the goods want to jump ahead on an evil's spawn.  Just win the guildwar, and the spawn is yours.<br>
<br>
Now, this does mean that one group would be able to dominate spawns that they're interested in, but only if the opposition couldn't find support from the other like-minded guilds.<br>
<br>
Of course, this would also mean that we'd have to have a system in place where, once all guilds on the server had agreed to a set of base rules, any guild that declared FFA would be blacklisted.  No res, no port, no group for members.  Harsh, but if you're gonna associate with Attilla the Hun, and you're gonna wear the 'Attilla's Huns' tag on your shirt, don't be suprised if the Roman's attack you on sight without getting to know you first.<br>
<br>
thoughts? <p>Denoi Fishwhiskers<BR>
